# Breadcrumb

- Contract: `component-specs/breadcrumb.json`, `docs/components/breadcrumb.md`. PDF in `titan-comp-doc/breadcrumb.pdf` wins on conflict.
- Current page is **never** a link; use `aria-current="page"` on the last segment.
- Overflow: `TitanBreadcrumb` collapses middle segments into a `…` menu; each item uses `onPress` — **parent state** must update `items` / `currentLabel` (e.g. truncate path to chosen segment). Same for visible ancestor links.
- Degraded hierarchy uses `resolutionState` (`loading|unavailable|deleted|restricted`) + optional `fallbackLabel`; these segments are always non-interactive (disabled) in both visible trail and `…` menu.
- Error handling strategy: **Hide > Rebuild > Fallback > Soft state**. Breadcrumb is structural navigation, not an aggressive error-feedback surface.
- Strip styling: `--breadcrumb-slot-bg`, `--breadcrumb-slot-min-height`, `--breadcrumb-slot-border-bottom` (default none) on `.breadcrumb-nav` (or parent strip: `.page-breadcrumb-host`, `.titan-app-breadcrumb-strip`).

# App shell

- **Navbar + sidebar + breadcrumb + main:** use `TitanAppShell` (`titan-app-*` classes). Navbar is full width; sidebar is left; breadcrumb + main share the column `viewport − sidebar width`. For a **fixed-height preview** (e.g. playground card), add `className="titan-app-root--fill-parent"` so the shell fills the container instead of `min-height: 100vh` (keeps sidebar collapse control visible).
- **Navbar only + breadcrumb + cards:** `TitanTwoUpOneDownLayout` or `main.page.page--flush-breadcrumb` with `page-breadcrumb-host`.
- Inner chrome max width: **1280** default, **1440** from **1440px** viewport — `.titan-app-content-inner` and `.page` (media query in `titan-compositions.css`).
